    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1021" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνι&lt;&gt;άζω</span></b> 
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνι&lt;&gt;́η</span>), ipf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνι&lt;&gt;́αζον</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">torment, annoy, weary</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            23.721</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 19.323</span></i>; usually
          intrans., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be tormented, wearied;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θῡμῷ ἀνῑάζων</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">agonized</span>
          at heart, of the mortally wounded Eurymachus, <i><span class="en">Od. 22.87</span></i>; similarly <i><span class="en">Il.
            21.270</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.460</span></i>; often
          weakened colloquially, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἠδή μοι ἀνῑάζουσιν
            ἑταῖροι</span>, ‘are worrying’ by this time, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.598</span></i>; ironically, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.300</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
